# Project layout

```
passreadyfinder/
├── src/
│   ├── config/              # product.config.ts
│   ├── engine/              # Intelligence + pipeline (risk-scorer.ts, finder, drafter…)
│   ├── server/              # Express API + job runner
│   ├── validation/          # Zod schemas
│   └── types/
├── dashboard/               # React mobile command center (Vite)
│   └── src/
│       ├── components/      # ActionCard.tsx, etc.
│       ├── App.tsx
│       └── main.tsx
├── public/                  # Legacy static control/review (until dashboard replaces)
└── .cursor/rules/
```

# Rules

- **Engine logic** lives in `src/engine/` — no React imports in engine files.
- **UI components** live in `dashboard/src/components/` — call API routes, never Turso directly.
- **Shared scoring** — import `calculateRiskScore` from engine path only in API/CLI, expose to UI via JSON.
